<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Insecure actress Yvonne Orji enlisted groomer Mickey West-Potts to shave the Black Lives Matter fist onto the side of her head for the 72nd Primetime Emmy Awards on Sunday night.</p>

<p>The Nigerian-born, Maryland-raised 36-year-old got fully glam to compete for the outstanding supporting actress in a comedy series trophy during the virtual ABC telecast.</p>

<p>Yvonne went head to head against seven other actresses for the Emmy, which ultimately went to Schitt's Creek star Annie Murphy. </p>

<p>'Nuff said!' Insecure actress Yvonne Orji enlisted groomer Mickey West-Potts to shave the Black Lives Matter fist onto the side of her head for the 72nd Primetime Emmy Awards on Sunday night</p>

<p>Orji got on the rooftop of an Atlanta hotel to pose in her Azzi &amp; Osta gown, Christian Louboutin heels, and David Yurman jewelry selected by stylist Apuje Kalu.</p>

<p>The Momma, I Made It comedian had the rest of her pixie cut coiffed by hairstylist Mary Daniels and make-up artist/esthetician Drini Marie made sure she was ready for her Zoom close-up.</p>

<p>Win or lose, Yvonne was certainly ready to party at the hotel with five others, even rolling out a red carpet.</p>

<p>'Because I don't know how not to be extra,' Orji - who boasts 1.3M social media followers - said via Instastory. </p>

